news.title: UK house prices post strongest start to year since 2005: Nationwide
news.para: House prices jumped by 0.8% in January, following a 1.1% increase in December. A Reuters poll of economists had pointed to a 0.6% increase last month.

news.title: Government proposes to tweak TDS norms on sale of immovable property
news.para: As per the Finance Bill, 2022, presented in Parliament along with the other Budget documents, the government proposes to amend Section 194-IA of the Income Tax Act, in order to remove inconsistency with Section 43CA and 50CA of the law.

news.title: Diluting FCA, environment ministry allows housing on one hectare forest land
news.para: Even as comments are being sought from the people by the MoEF&CC to amend the FCA, the Union environment ministry is on a dilution-spree of the FCA rules which are likely to benefit project proponents.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body reduces rebate on property tax for GIDCs
news.para: ​The standing committee will give a formal approval to the proposal on Thursday. It was in early January that the AMC had placed a proposal before its standing committee of revising the rebate rate from 75% to 50%.

news.title: Budget 2022: Government proposes to set up expert committee for urban planning
news.para: ​"By the time of India @ 100, nearly half our population is likely to be living in urban areas. To prepare for this, orderly urban development is of critical importance. This will help realize the country's economic potential, including livelihood opportunities for the demographic dividend," she said.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board to start online services for transfer of properties
news.para: ​The three services include NOC for transfer deed of lease rights; transfer of leasehold property on registered transfer-deed of lease rights; and transfer of freehold property through sale/gift/transfer deeds.

news.title: Scope of single-window portal for giving green nod to projects to be expanded: FM
news.para: ​PARIVESH is a web-based, role-based workflow app developed for online submission and monitoring of proposals submitted by the proponents for seeking environment, forest, wildlife and coastal regulation zone (CRZ) clearances from central, state and district-level authorities.

news.title: Kochi: Survey for proposed GIFT city land acquisition to be over next week
news.para: T Devarajan, the special tahsildar appointed for the land acquisition, said the survey process is nearing completion and it would be concluded within a week.

news.title: Budget 2022: 80 lakh houses to be completed in FY23 under PMAY; Rs 48,000 crore allocated
news.para: ​In her budget speech, the minister said: "In 2022-23, 80 lakh houses will be completed for the identified eligible beneficiaries of PM Awas Yojana, both rural and urban. Rs 48,000 crore is allocated for this purpose."

news.title: Provide pucca house to each eligible family: Bihar CM to officials
news.para: While chairing a meeting to review the progress of the PMAY-G and the MMGAY in the state, he also asked the officials to ensure that not a single eligible beneficiary is left out from getting a pucca house under either of the two schemes.

news.title: Centre ignored demand for synchronisation of rural housing data with Awaas+: Odisha minister
news.para: ​He also accused the central government of ignoring a promise made in May 2019 to Odisha in the aftermath of cyclonic storm Fani for approval of 1.84 lakh houses under the special Pradhan Mantri Awaas Yojana-Gramin programme.

news.title: Hariom Pipe Industries gets Sebi's go ahead to raise funds via IPO
news.para: Hariom Pipe Industries, which had filed preliminary IPO papers with Sebi in September 2021, obtained its observation letter on January 25, 2022, an update with Sebi showed on Monday.

news.title: Centre summons Maharashtra government officials for failing to implement PMAY scheme
news.para: Claiming that less than 1% of the total number of applicants have been allotted houses under the PMAY, Jaleel said the Union government, as well as the bureaucrats, have made a fool of the poor people who dreamed of having their own home.

news.title: Nitin Raut directs Nagpur civic body to waive smart city's charges levied on PAPs
news.para: Raut organized a meeting between PAPs, plot owners and NMC officials, including municipal commissioner Radhakrishnan B, NSSCDCL and collector R Vimala on Monday. Congress corporator Praful Gudadhe led the delegation of the PAPs.

news.title: DTCP to take land pooling route to develop two sectors in Sohna
news.para: The department is sending a land pooling proposal to the Haryana Shahri Vikas Pradhikaran (HSVP) chief administrator in Chandigarh for final approval. A detailed survey is likely after that.
